# Gotchas & Non-Obvious Decisions

## Episode Config

### `xUrl` / `youtubeUrl` — not `url`
The episode config uses **two separate URL fields**, not a single `url`. This was refactored in April 2026 to support multi-platform listings.

```typescript
// WRONG — this field no longer exists
{ url: "https://x.com/..." }

// CORRECT
{ xUrl: "https://x.com/...", youtubeUrl: "https://www.youtube.com/..." }
```

Omit the field entirely (don't set to `""`) if the link isn't available. The UI handles `undefined` gracefully.

### Episode numbers are derived, not stored

The display episode number is calculated from the array index:
```tsx
const epNum = String(total - i).padStart(2, "0");
```

Do **not** try to encode the episode number in the object or the render logic. Just keep the array in descending order (newest first).

### `key` prop uses `ep.title`, not `ep.url`

The map key was previously `ep.url`. After the refactor to `xUrl`/`youtubeUrl`, it was changed to `ep.title`. If you see a React key warning, check this first.

