## UI / Component

### `guestTitle` renders without `guestCompany`

Early code required **both** `guestTitle` and `guestCompany` to render the subtitle line:
```tsx
// OLD — broken for guests with no company
{ep.guestTitle && ep.guestCompany && (...)}

// CURRENT — correct
{ep.guestTitle && (
  <span>
    {ep.guestTitle}{ep.guestCompany && <> &middot; {ep.guestCompany}</>}
  </span>
)}
```

If you ever see a guest's title missing on the site, check this condition. `guestTitle` alone is sufficient; `guestCompany` is optional.

### Episode row is a `div`, not an `<a>`

The entire episode row used to be a single `<a>` tag. It was changed to a `<div>` when multi-platform links were added (you can't nest `<a>` inside `<a>`). The play button is now the `<a>` to the primary URL. Platform pill badges are separate `<a>` tags.

Don't revert to wrapping the whole row in an anchor — it would break the pills.

### Play button priority: YouTube first

```tsx
const primaryUrl = ep.youtubeUrl || ep.xUrl;
```

YouTube is preferred over X as the primary platform. This is intentional — YouTube is the more accessible platform for new listeners.

