## Config Naming

### `siteConfig.youtubeUrl` vs `ep.youtubeUrl` — two different things

These look the same but are completely different:

| Field | What it is |
|-------|-----------|
| `siteConfig.youtubeUrl` | The channel URL: `https://www.youtube.com/@TheSuperlativePodcast` — used in the hero, episodes header, and footer |
| `ep.youtubeUrl` | A specific episode's YouTube video link: `https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=XXXX` |

The footer YouTube link uses `siteConfig.youtubeUrl` and auto-disables (`pointer-events-none opacity-20`) if the value is empty. It was in this disabled state until the channel URL was added in April 2026.

### `episodeFeed` config block

`siteConfig.episodeFeed` is a separate config block in `config.ts` that controls an embedded X timeline or YouTube feed elsewhere on the page — it is **not** the episode listing. It has its own `source`, `xHandle`, and `youtubePlaylistId` fields. Don't confuse it with the `episodes` array.

