## Data Sourcing

### Notion Episodes DB vs Podcast Artifacts DB

Two separate Notion databases — don't confuse them:

| Database | Purpose |
|----------|---------|
| **Episodes** (ID: `3344613294668035aa4dd29efc7b4696`) | Guest records, episode numbers, status, emails |
| **Podcast Artifacts** (ID: `33346132946680cd836ec3d130e1e5cf`) | Promotion kits, content assets — X broadcast links are embedded in artifact page content |

Guest roles often aren't in the Episodes DB — check Attio CRM (`people` object) if `Firm or Company` is blank.

### YouTube channel has two tabs

When sourcing YouTube links, check **both**:
- `/videos` — uploaded recordings
- `/streams` (Live tab) — archived livestreams

Episodes recorded before YouTube streaming was active will only have X links. As of April 2026: Episodes 5, 6, 7, 8 are X-only.

### YouTube video IDs live in `ytInitialData`

The YouTube channel page embeds all video metadata in a JSON blob in the page HTML. To reliably extract video URLs, fetch the page and parse `ytInitialData` — don't try to scrape visible HTML elements.

