## Design Decisions

### "Live on X" badge was removed

The hero section previously had a pulsing red "Live on X" badge. It was removed because the show now streams on both X and YouTube, and a permanent "live" badge was misleading when no episode is actively streaming.

### DaVinci Jeremie has no `guestCompany`

This is intentional. DaVinci's personal brand (Bitcoin OG, ~900K YouTube subscribers) is larger than any company he's associated with. Using a company name would undersell him. His `guestTitle` is `"Bitcoin Pioneer & Crypto Educator"` and `guestCompany` is `""`.

Apply the same logic to any future guest where the person is bigger than the org.

### YouTube channel link appears in three places

1. Hero — subtle secondary link below the main CTA
2. Episodes section header — "Subscribe" link with YouTube icon
3. Footer — part of the social links nav

This was deliberate — the channel was newly launched and needed visibility. Don't remove any of these without considering the user's goal of driving YouTube subscribers.

